This is actually one of the most interesting missing capabilities in current AI systems.

Today AI mostly outputs:

* Text
* Images
* Audio
* Code

But humans don’t naturally consume information that way.

Humans consume:

Narrative + Voice + Motion + Visuals + Timing + Music + Emphasis + Context

In other words:

Video is the natural compression format for human learning.

What you’re describing is essentially:

Multimodal Synthesis Engine (MSE)

Input:

“How does the CPG market work for getting Wild Hawg into stores?”

Output:
A complete custom 7-minute YouTube-quality explainer video.

Not a template.

Not a stock animation.

A bespoke generated lesson.

